OL,5, A hospital worker who disarmed a man   
OL,6, who walked into an A&E brandishing an  
OL,7, imitation gun and demanding to be seen 
OL,8, has been given a bravery award.        
OL,10,FSecurity officer Dean Priestley did not
OL,11,Fknow the gun was a replica when the man
OL,12,Fpointed it at a porter at Bradford     
OL,13,FRoyal Infirmary in October 2020.       
OL,15,FMr Priestley calmly asked the man to   
OL,16,Fhand him the weapon and sat with him.  
OL,18,FHe said he had felt "a million times   
OL,19,Fmore nervous" about collecting his     
OL,20,Fbravery medal than during the incident.
